types.name: nftTransfer
types.description: The nftTransfer model is built to record and chronicle the transfer of NFTs between addresses. This model is crucial in tracing the movement of an NFT, especially when validating that an event pass has reached its intended recipient. Such a system facilitates debugging and reduces the need for excessive querying of our indexer. Entries in this table are populated through two primary avenues: either via an activity webhook responding to real-time NFT transfers or through a regular cron job as a failsafe, ensuring data integrity even if the webhook fails to capture certain events.

fields.name: blockNumber
fields.description: The specific block on the blockchain where this transfer was recorded. Allows for pinpointing the exact point of transfer in the blockchain's history.

fields.name: chainId
fields.description: Indicates the specific blockchain or network where the NFT resides. Useful in a multi-chain environment to distinguish between various chains.

fields.name: contractAddress
fields.description: Identifies the smart contract associated with the NFT. This provides a direct link to the NFT's origin and behavior on the blockchain.

fields.name: contractAddress
fields.description: Identifies the smart contract associated with the NFT. This provides a direct link to the NFT's origin and behavior on the blockchain.

fields.name: eventId
fields.description: Refers to the associated event ID for which the NFT was transferred. Ties the NFT transfer to a particular event in the platform.

fields.name: eventPassId
fields.description: Denotes the specific Event Pass associated with the NFT. Helps in tracking the lifecycle of a particular event pass.

fields.name: fromAddress
fields.description: Denotes the source address from which the NFT was transferred. Essential to trace the sender in the NFT's movement.

fields.name: organizerId
fields.description: Identifies the organizer who facilitated the event linked to the NFT transfer. Aids in associating NFT movements with specific organizers.

fields.name: toAddress
fields.description: Specifies the destination address receiving the NFT. Critical for determining the current holder of the NFT.

fields.name: tokenId
fields.description: The unique identifier for the NFT within its associated smart contract. Maintains a constant reference to the NFT across platforms.

fields.name: transactionHash
fields.description: Represents the unique hash of the transaction in which the NFT was transferred. Ensures traceability and verification on the blockchain.
